        <h2>Event Details</h2>
        <p>Do-It-Ourselves Fest is one day of workshops celebrating DIY culture, art, music, and learning through mutual aid.</p>
        <p>DIO Fest is about what we can do ourselves, for ourselves and one another. Itâ€™s about what we are all capable of when we come together as one.</p>
        <p>
            We are drawing on a rich history; this is the fourth DIO Fest that has been held in Lincoln, from a small event at the Bike Kitchen in 2013, growing a bit in 2015 at the Commons, to a jam-packed 3-day event at the Bay in 2017.
            This year, we're back at the Bay, for just one day.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Schedule</h2>
        <p>
            Check in/mingling starts at 9am, and we'll kick off at 9:45am. We'll go throughout the day and finish off with several sets of live, local music starting at 5:00pm.
            Attendance is free, all ages are welcome. No alcohol on-site, please.
        </p>
