        <h2>Workshops this year include:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Disaster Preparedness Through Community & Connection</li>
            <li>Making It a Banner Event: Projectors, Sheets, and the Streets with Lou Braatz</li>
            <li>Menstrual Cycle 101: Conception, Contraception, and Curiosity with Diane</li>
            <li>Advanced Mental Health Directives with MarLee</li>
            <li>Know Your Rights</li>
            <li>and more!!</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Accessibility Info:</h2>
        <p>
            The event will primarily be taking place indoors in a wheelchair-friendly space. As the covid pandemic is ongoing and we want to be as inclusive as we can to our at-risk community members, masks are highly encouraged. However, there will be opportunities for snacks and drinks - you're welcome to step outside for those breaks if you'd like.
        </p>
